  • public class mammal
extends animal

    mammal

    This class extends the animal class file.

    This file allows for the creation of animals and, more specifically, mammals.

    This class has to be in tandem with the animal class.

    Since:
    2017-12-09
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Joshua Ong

    • Method Detail

      • feedyoung

        public void feedyoung()
        Determines if the mammal can feed its young or not.

        If intMilk is greater than 0, the mammal can feed its young

        If intMilk equals 0, the mammal cannot feed its young.

      • fight

        public void fight()
        Allows the mammal to fight.

      • think

        public void think()
        Lets the mammal think.

        If the Brain to Body ratio is above 0.25, the mammal can think.

        If the Brain to Body ratio is below 0.25, the mammal cannot think.

      • reproduce

        public void reproduce()
        Determines whether or not the mammal can reproduce.

        If the mammal's gender is male, it cannot reproduce.

        If the mammal's gender is female, it can reproduce.

        Overrides:
        reproduce in class animal
